%20subscriptions%20is%20this%20one%3A%20Spotify%20really%2C%20really%20wants%20to%20do%20stuff%20beyond%20selling%20music%20subscriptions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20just%20selling%20music%20subscriptions%20is%20a%20really%20hard%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20that's%20worth%20spelling%20out%20here%2C%20very%20briefly%3A%20The%20music%20subscription%20service%20is%20really%20hard%20because%20%3Cem%3Eyour%20costs%20scale%20along%20with%20your%20success%3C%2Fem%3E.%20As%20Spotify%20sells%20more%20subscriptions%2C%20and%20generates%20more%20streams%2C%20the%20amount%20of%20money%20it%20has%20to%20pay%20music%20labels%20and%20other%20rights%20owners%20increases%20alongside%20of%20it.%20The%20company%20says%20it%20shells%20out%2070%20cents%20to%20music%20owners%20for%20every%20dollar%20it%20generates%2C%20primarily%20from%20the%20226%20million%20subscribers%20it%20has%20acquired%20worldwide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20radically%20different%20than%20other%20digital%20subscription%20businesses%2C%20like%20video%20or%20software%2C%20where%20a%20company%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnetflix-viewership-data-takeaways-ads-business-strategy-future-streaming-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENetflix%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20Microsoft%20can%20pay%20once%20to%20license%20a%20movie%20or%20create%20a%20new%20version%20of%20Excel%2C%20and%20sell%20it%20an%20unlimited%20number%20of%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20explains%20why%20Spotify%20is%20by%20far%20the%20biggest%20independent%20music%20streaming%20service.%20Its%20real%20rivals%20are%20the%20services%20run%20by%20the%20likes%20of%20Apple%20and%20Google%2C%20who%20view%20music%20as%20a%20sidelight%20at%20best%20and%20don't%20need%20to%20worry%20about%20generating%20real%20profit%20from%20it%2C%20or%20any%20profit%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20it%20also%20explains%20why%2C%20while%20music%20industry%20insiders%20like%20to%20bat%20around%20the%20idea%20of%20Spotify%20as%20an%20acquisition%20target%2C%20it's%20hard%20to%20imagine%20that%20actually%20happening%3A%20Who%20wants%20a%20business%20that's%20so%20hard%20to%20make%20money%20in%3F%20And%20if%20they%20did%2C%20why%20not%20build%20their%20own%20version%2C%20as%20both%20Google%20and%20Apple%20have%20done%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20good%20news%20for%20Spotify%2C%20though.%20For%20starters%2C%20investors%20do%20like%20the%20story%20the%20company%20has%20been%20telling.%20After%20plummeting%20from%20a%20pandemic%2Ftech%20frenzy%20high%2C%20Spotify%20shares%20have%20been%20steadily%20increasing%20for%20some%20time%2C%20and%20have%20more%20than%20doubled%20in%20the%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20even%20if%20fickle%20investors%20decide%20that%20they're%20once%20again%20skeptical%20about%20Spotify's%20chances%2C%20there's%20one%20group%20that's%20always%20going%20to%20root%20for%20them%20%E2%80%94%20or%20at%20least%20root%20for%20them%20not%20to%20fail.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20the%20big%20music%20labels%2C%20which%20don't%20always%20love%20Spotify%20but%20are%20most%20definitely%20locked%20in%20a%20co-dependent%20relationship%20with%20them%3A%20Spotify%20needs%20the%20big%20three%20music%20labels%20(Sony%2C%20Warner%2C%20and%20Universal)%20along%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmerlinnetwork.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMerlin%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20represents%20a%20lot%20of%20indie%20labels%2C%20to%20supply%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20the%20music%20it%20streams.%20And%20the%20labels%20need%20Spotify%20to%20keep%20finding%20more%20people%20to%20pay%20for%20music.%20They%20can't%20afford%20to%20let%20it%20fail.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspotify-streaming-music-brutal-business-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705667401000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657382f10ec98e92f74dca17%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22