%2C%20especially%20from%20Amazon%2C%20are%20pricey.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Leslie%20Redmond%2C%2037%2C%20about%20her%20experience%20moving%20from%20Alaska%20to%20Winnipeg%2C%20a%20city%20of%20around%20750%2C000%20residents%20in%20the%20center%20of%20Canada.%20She%20is%20an%20assistant%20professor%20of%20food%20and%20human%20nutritional%20sciences%20in%20the%20Faculty%20of%20Agricultural%20and%20Food%20Sciences%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Manitoba.%20The%20conversation%20was%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWinnipeg%20is%20known%20as%20the%20cultural%20capital%20of%20Canada.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20large%20newcomer%20population%20from%20all%20areas%20%E2%80%94%20a%20lot%20of%20Asian%20countries.%20There's%20a%20really%20large%20Filipino%20population%20here.%20There's%20a%20really%20big%20Ukrainian%20population%20and%20a%20really%20big%20Polish%20population.%20So%20there%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20flavors%20and%20foods%20that%20are%20really%20ubiquitous%20up%20here%20that%20I%20wouldn't%20have%20had%20in%20the%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECulture%20is%20a%20big%20thing%20here%2C%20and%20it's%20widely%20appreciated.%20They%20have%20a%20festival%20every%20summer%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffolklorama.ca%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFolklorama%3C%2Fa%3E%20where%20all%20these%20different%20cultural%20centers%20put%20on%20performances%20and%20sell%20their%20food.%20You%20go%20and%20learn%20about%20their%20customs%20and%20their%20culture%2C%20and%20that%20draws%20a%20lot%20of%20people%2C%20even%20from%20North%20Dakota.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EIt's%20not%20the%20paradise%20Americans%20expect%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20perfect.%20Especially%20since%20moving%20here%2C%20I've%20learned%20they%20have%20their%20own%20issues.%20It's%20not%20some%20paradise%20that%20Americans%20envision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou're%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20continent%20here.%20It's%20not%20Vancouver%2C%20not%20Quebec.%20There%20is%20a%20housing%20shortage%2C%20but%20it%20is%20still%20a%20low%20cost%20of%20living%2C%20relatively%20speaking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20bought%20our%20house%20for%20a%20little%20over%20%24500%2C000%20CAD%20(or%20about%20%24370%2C000)%20just%20over%20a%20year%20ago.%20It%20was%20right%20after%20things%20had%20really%20peaked.%20By%20peaked%2C%20I%20mean%20there%20were%20houses%20that'd%20be%20on%20the%20market%20a%20day%2C%20or%20within%20a%20certain%20asking%20price%20bracket%20you'd%20go%20and%20there'd%20be%20like%2030%20people%20at%20an%20open%20house%2C%20or%20there%20were%20bidding%20wars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20the%20case%20across%20Canada%20%E2%80%94%20and%20across%20the%20US%20%E2%80%94%20but%20I%20think%20that's%20kind%20of%20slowed%20down%20a%20little%20bit%20now.%20But%20housing's%20very%20expensive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlaska's%20not%20a%20good%20comparison%20or%20representative%20of%20the%20US%20because%20everything's%20more%20expensive%20up%20there%2C%20too.%20I%20would%20say%20Winnipeg%20is%20pretty%20equivalent%20to%20Alaska%2C%20but%20Alaska%20is%20higher%20than%20what%20you%20would%20find%20in%20the%20lower%2048.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221536%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20posing%20in%20knee-high%20snow%20in%20front%20of%20a%20sign%20in%20Canada.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a84b0adcdb354a985868cf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERedmond%20visiting%20Yukon%2C%20Canada.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Leslie%20Redmond.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20miss%20Amazon.%20In%20the%20States%2C%20it's%20way%20cheaper.%20When%20I%20logged%20on%20to%20Amazon%20to%20buy%20things%20the%20first%20couple%20of%20times%20here%2C%20I%20was%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BWhy%20is%20this%20so%20expensive%3F%26quot%3B%20And%20then%20I%20would%20log%20onto%20my%20US%20account%20and%20it's%20like%20half%20the%20price.%20So%20that%20was%20a%20little%20disappointing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20just%20the%20silliest%20of%20things%2C%20but%20when%20going%20to%20the%20store%20in%20the%20US%2C%20there%20are%20so%20many%20different%20varieties%20of%20things.%20Here%20there%20are%20a%20few%20options.%20I%20didn't%20realize%20that%20was%20a%20luxury%20in%20the%20US%20until%20I%20came%20here%20and%20my%20choices%20were%20limited.%20In%20Winnipeg%2C%20we're%20about%20two%20hours%20from%20North%20Dakota%2C%20so%20sometimes%20we'll%20go%20down%20to%20Grand%20Forks%20just%20to%20go%20to%20Target%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it's%20a%20big%20deal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20see%20all%20these%20other%20Canadians%20there%2C%20too.%20And%20my%20husband%20always%20mentions%2C%20even%20since%20he%20was%20a%20kid%2C%20the%20cereal%20aisle%20astounds%20him.%20So%20any%20time%20we're%20in%20Target%20in%20Grand%20Forks%2C%20there's%20just%20all%20these%20Canadians%20in%20the%20cereal%20aisle%20picking%20out%20their%20cereal%20because%20there%20are%20so%20many%20choices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20lived%20in%20a%20lot%20of%20interesting%20places%2C%20but%20I%20never%20thought%20I'd%20live%20in%20the%20prairie.%20Winnipeg%20is%20flat%20and%20there%20is%20very%20little%20geographical%20variation.%20There%20are%20parts%20of%20Manitoba%20that%20have%20forests%20and%20that%20have%20some%20hills%2C%20and%20there%20are%20lots%20and%20lots%20and%20lots%20of%20lakes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221647%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20and%20a%20woman%20standing%20in%20front%20of%20a%20sign%20that%20reads%20%26quot%3BCentre%20of%2Fdu%20Canada.%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a84a9b43bb77284b9dee6e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221239%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERedmond%20and%20her%20husband%20Justin%20Reitsma.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Leslie%20Redmond.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20love%20their%20cabins%20on%20the%20lakes%20here%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it%20is%20beautiful%20%E2%80%94%20but%20for%20me%2C%20I%20think%20that%20was%20the%20hardest%20adjustment.%20Going%20from%20a%20very%20dramatic%2C%20rugged%2C%20mountainous%2C%20oceanside%20environment%20to%20a%20very%20flat%20middle%20of%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20closest%20city%20is%20two%20hours%20away.%20I%20can't%20quote%20you%20on%20the%20population%2C%20but%20it's%20very%20small%2C%20but%20it's%20what%20qualifies%20as%20an%20urban%20area%20in%20Manitoba.%20I%20think%20there%20are%20Midwestern%20cities%20in%20the%20US%20where%20it's%20the%20exact%20same%20situation%3A%20You're%20in%20a%20big%20city%2C%20but%20there%20are%20no%20big%20cities%20around%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou're%20landlocked%20%E2%80%94%20the%20equivalent%20of%20a%20flyover%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20had%20thought%20of%20living%20in%20Canada%20even%20before%20it%20became%20an%20option%20for%20me%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20prior%20to%20dating%20a%20Canadian%2C%20I%20was%20excited%20to%20move%20to%20Canada.%20My%20friends%20and%20I%20had%20always%20joked%2C%20%26quot%3BOh%2C%20we%20should%20just%20move%20to%20Canada.%26quot%3B%20So%20it%20had%20crossed%20my%20mind%2C%20but%20not%20seriously.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20I%20was%20in%20a%20serious%20relationship%20and%20we%20knew%20we%20were%20going%20to%20get%20married%2C%20I%20wasn't%20hesitant%20at%20all.%20I%20was%20excited%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20my%20particular%20position%20in%20academia%2C%20I%20work%20with%20Indigenous%20populations.%20Canada%20still%20has%20a%20really%20long%20way%20to%20go%2C%20as%20far%20as%20reconciliation%20with%20Indigenous%20communities.%20But%2C%20in%20my%20experience%20now%20working%20in%20the%20US%20and%20Canada%2C%20Canada's%20far%20ahead%20of%20the%20US%20as%20far%20as%20that's%20concerned%20in%20academia%20and%20the%20research%20realm.%20That%20was%20really%20a%20positive%20thing%20coming%20here%20for%20my%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20excited%20about%20free%20healthcare.%20Of%20course%2C%20you%20pay%20for%20it%20in%20taxes%2C%20but%20you%20hear%20about%20that%20and%20you%20hear%20about%20the%20really%20generous%20maternity%20leave.%20I%20knew%20there%20were%20higher%20taxes%20here%20coming%20into%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20that%20collectivist%20mentality%20%E2%80%94%20if%20it's%20good%20for%20the%20group%2C%20it's%20good%20for%20me%20%E2%80%94%20which%20I%20think%20is%20more%20pervasive%20in%20Canada.%20Which%20is%20why%20most%20people%20here%20are%20okay%20with%20socialized%20healthcare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20want%20to%20have%20kids%20until%20I%20officially%20became%20a%20permanent%20resident%20in%20the%20healthcare%20system.%20I%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20friends%20my%20age%20having%20kids%20in%20the%20States%20%E2%80%94%20just%20hearing%20from%20them%20the%20medical%20bills%20and%20the%20things%20they%20have%20to%20go%20through.%20And%20heaven%20forbid%20something%20goes%20wrong%20during%20labor%2C%20and%20you%20have%20to%20stay%20in%20the%20NICU%20for%2010%20days.%20The%20cost%20just%20adds%20up.%20Here%2C%20if%20anything%20happened%2C%20they're%20covered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20politics%20here%2C%20it's%20just%20not%20so%20bipartisan.%20There%20are%20many%20more%20perspectives.%20I%20think%20it's%20more%20of%20an%20even%20playing%20field.%20So%20it's%20not%20that%20there%20isn't%20politics%2C%20it's%20just%20different.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20dating%20my%20husband%20when%20it%20was%20election%20season%20in%20the%20US%2C%20and%20I%20felt%20every%20time%20I%20went%20into%20the%20Yukon%2C%20where%20he%20lived%20before%20we%20moved%2C%20it%20was%20a%20relief%20because%20it%20was%20like%20I%20got%20to%20be%20immediately%20shielded%20from%20all%20the%20election%20drama%20that%20was%20happening%20in%20the%20US.%20It%20wasn't%20on%20the%20news%20as%20much.%20I%20could%20ignore%20it%20if%20I%20wanted%20to%2C%20whereas%20in%20Alaska%2C%20it%20was%20in%20my%20face%20all%20the%20time.%20It%20just%20got%20so%20tiresome%20and%20anxiety-inducing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20very%20easy%20for%20someone%20in%20the%20US%20to%20move%20to%20Canada.%20It's%20not%20so%20easy%2C%20maybe%2C%20from%20other%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20I%20do%20feel%20very%20privileged%20that%20I%20was%20able%20to%20pick%20up%20and%20move.%20Not%20everybody%20can%20do%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-to-canada-healthcare-amazon-not-paradise-welcoming-community-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705662781000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a84b3d6979d737182425f0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-to-canada-healthcare-amazon-not-paradise-welcoming-community-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Leslie%20Redmond%2C%2037%2C%20said%20Canada%20is%20great%20even%20if%20it%20isn't%20the%20paradise%20Americans%20envision.%20She%20still%20returns%20to%20the%20US%20for%20Target's%20cereal%20aisle.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jpandy%40insider.com%20(Jordan%20Pandy)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A17%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-to-canada-healthcare-amazon-not-paradise-welcoming-community-2024-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22With%20Golden%20Bow%20And%20Arrow%2C%20Ram%20Lalla's%201st%20Complete%20Look%20Revealed%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERam%20Temple%20Inauguration%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20Lord%20Ram%20idol%20which%20has%20been%20placed%20at%20the%20Ayodhya%20Temple%20was%20revealed%20today%2C%20days%20ahead%20of%20the%20consecration%20ceremony%20on%20Monday.%20The%20idol%20depicts%20Lord%20Ram%20as%20a%20five-year-old%20child%20in%20a%20standing%20posture%20holding%20a%20golden%20bow%20and%20arrow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2051-inch%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld