2F01%2F09152825%2FUntitled-design-3-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20refused%20to%20extend%20the%20time%20for%20surrender%20of%20the%2011%20convicts%20in%20the%20Bilkis%20Bano%20case%20who%20have%20been%20out%20on%20remission.%20Now%2C%20they%20have%20to%20surrender%20as%20per%20the%20original%20deadline%20on%20Sunday%2C%20January%2021%2C%20following%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20ruling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20reasons%20cited%20by%20applicants%20to%20seek%20postponement%20of%20surrender%20and%20report%20back%20to%20jail%20have%20no%20merit%20in%20as%20much%20as%20those%20reasons%20in%20no%20way%20prevent%20them%20from%20complying%20with%20our%20directions%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20Bench%20of%20Justice%20B.V.%20Nagarathna%20and%20Justice%20Ujjal%20Bhuyan%20said%2C%20according%20to%20India%20Today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20citing%20various%20reasons%2C%20including%20health%20and%20family%20responsibilities%2C%2010%20of%20the%2011%20convicts%20had%20moved%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20seeking%20more%20time%20to%20surrender.%20The%20top%20court%2C%20agreeing%20to%20hear%20their%20pleas%2C%20had%20clubbed%20all%20of%20their%20petitions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20deadline%20for%20their%20surrender%20expires%20on%20Sunday%2C%20January%2021.%20The%20court%20had%20said%20it%20would%20hear%20their%20petitions%20once%20the%20Bench%20that%20scrapped%20their%20remission%20on%20January%208%20is%20reconstituted%20by%20the%20chief%20justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSince%20the%20bench%20has%20to%20be%20reconstituted%2C%20registry%20to%20seek%20orders%20from%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20(CJI)%20for%20reconstitution%20of%20the%20Bench%20as%20the%20time%20(to%20surrender)%20expires%20on%20Sunday%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20top%20court%20had%20said%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2F10-bilkis-case-convicts-ask-supreme-court-for-more-time-to-surrender-101705614371674.html%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20the%3Cem%3E%20Hindustan%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20January%208%2C%20a%20Bench%20of%20Justice%20B.V.%20Nagarathna%20and%20Justice%20Ujjal%20Bhuyan%20had%20scrapped%20the%20remission%20of%20the%20convicts%20and%20ordered%20them%20to%20surrender%20in%20two%20weeks.%20The%20Bench%20had%20then%20said%20the%20Gujarat%20government%20by%20executing%20remission%20had%20%E2%80%9Cusurped%E2%80%9D%20the%20power%20of%20the%20government%20in%20Maharashtra%2C%20where%20the%20matter%20is%20being%20adjudicated.%20It%20had%20also%20pulled%20the%20Gujarat%20government%20noting%20that%20the%20remission%20was%20granted%20by%20%E2%80%9Cplaying%20fraud%E2%80%9D%20on%20the%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETill%20Thursday%2C%20January%2018%20evening%2C%2010%20of%20the%2011%20convicts%20had%20moved%20the%20court%20separately.%20They%20sought%20more%20time%20for%20surrender%2C%20on%20the%20account%20of%20meeting%20family%20responsibilities%2C%20caring%20for%20aged%20parents%2C%20harvesting%20of%20winter%20crops%2C%20and%20health%20conditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENine%20of%20the%2011%20convicts%20namely%20Chandana%2C%20Mitesh%20Chimanlal%20Bhatt%2C%20Pradip%20Ramanlal%20Modhiya%2C%20Bipinchand%20Kaniyalal%20Joshi%2C%20Radheyshyam%20Bhagwandas%20Shah%2C%20Rajubhai%20Babulal%20Soni%2C%20Jaswantbhai%20Chaturbhai%20Nai%2C%20Kesharbhai%20Khimabhai%20Vohania%20and%20Shaileshbhai%20Chimanlal%20Bhatt%20sought%20an%20additional%20six%20weeks%20to%20surrender.%20For%20his%20part%2C%C2%A0Govindbhai%20Nai%20has%20sought%20an%20extra%20time%20of%20four%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20the%20winter%20crops%20produced%20by%20the%20applicant%20are%20ready%20for%20harvesting%20and%20other%20processes%2C%20the%20applicant%20needs%20five%20to%20six%20weeks%20for%20such%20harvesting%20and%20other%20processes%20to%20be%20completed%2C%E2%80%9D%20Mitesh%20Bhatt%20said%20in%20his%20application%20filed%20on%20Wednesday%20night%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3EHT%3C%2Fem%3E%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20convict%20Chandana%20(58)%20cited%20health%20issues%2C%20saying%20that%20he%20had%20recently%20undergone%20an%20angiogram%20and%20is%20on%20medication.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20this%20condition%20to%20surrender%20within%20time%20directed%20by%20this%20court%20will%20be%20adverse%20not%20only%20to%20his%20mental%20health%20but%20will%20affect%20him%20physically%20severely%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilar%20reasons%20have%20been%20cited%20by%20another%20convict%20Joshi%2C%20who%20says%20that%20he%20had%20a%20leg%20surgery%20recently%2C%20which%20according%20to%20him%2C%20makes%20him%20partially%20handicapped.%20Modhiya%20said%20he%20had%20undergone%20lung%20surgery%20recently.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20convicts%20also%20cited%20marriageable-age%20children%20as%20a%20reason%20for%20seeking%20more%20time%20to%20surrender.%20They%20say%20if%20they%20are%20given%20additional%20time%20they%20would%20be%20in%20a%20position%20to%20discharge%20their%20responsibilities%20as%20a%20family%20member.%20Some%20even%20cited%20their%20aged%20parents%20and%20their%20medical%20condition%20as%20a%20reason%20for%20seeking%20more%20time.%20A%20couple%20of%20them%20also%20said%20their%20families%20are%20dependent%20on%20agriculture%2C%20hence%20it%20would%20be%20better%20for%20them%20to%20be%20with%20the%20families%20when%20the%20upcoming%20winter%20crop%20is%20harvested.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705662000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F09152825%2FUntitled-design-3-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fhealth-family-reasons-and-more-convicts-in-the-bilkis-bano-case-move-sc-for-more-time-to-surrender%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20January%208%20had%20scrapped%20the%20remission%20granted%20to%20the%2011%20convicts%20and%20asked%20them%20to%20surrender%20in%20two%20weeks.%20The%20deadline%