20and%20a%20slew%20of%20media%20appearances%20followed%2C%20from%20writeups%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2021%2F04%2F19%2Fdining%2Ffishwife-smoked-trout.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20a%20tastefully%20muted%20photo%20shoot%20in%20Cond%C3%A9%20Nast%20Traveller%20under%20the%20headline%20%26quot%3BMeet%20the%20Women%20Making%20Tinned%20Fish%20Cool.%26quot%3B%20In%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nylon.com%2Flife%2Ftinned-fish-snack-internet-obsession%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%3Cspan%3Ean%20interview%20with%20NYLON%20in%202021%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20Goldfarb%20declared%3A%20%26quot%3BTinned%20fish%20is%20the%20ultimate%20hot%20girl%20food%2C%26quot%3B%20leading%20to%20a%20wave%20of%20trend%20stories%20about%20what%20was%20and%20wasn't%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vice.com%2Fen%2Farticle%2F4avqpj%2Fwhy-is-tinned-fish-hot-girl-food-now%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3Bhot%20girl%20food.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20buzz%20culminated%20with%20Fishwife%20appearing%20on%20Shark%20Tank's%20latest%20episode%2C%20where%20the%20brand%20hooked%20two%20investors%20in%20a%20deal%20valuing%20the%20company%20at%20%245%20million%20%E2%80%94%20but%20the%20absence%20of%20one%20of%20the%20two%20beloved%20co-founders%20made%20some%20sense%20blood%20was%20in%20the%20water.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMillstein%20said%20on%20the%20ABC%20program%20that%20her%20premium%20preserved%20fish%20company%20has%20grown%20to%20about%20%245.8%20million%20in%20annual%20sales.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20unapologetically%20flipping%20the%20entire%20seafood%20industry%20on%20its%20tail%20in%20a%20bold%2C%20beautiful%2C%20and%20brazen%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20Plus%2C%20she%20added%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20TikTok%20trend%20is%20'hot%20girls%20eat%20tinned%20fish.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHer%20pitch%20landed%20her%20a%20deal%20with%20investors%20Lori%20Greiner%20and%20Candice%20Nelson%20on%20an%20episode%20that%20aired%20January%2012.%20But%20Millstein%20appeared%20on%20the%20show%20without%20Goldfarb%2C%20casting%20a%20spotlight%20on%20a%20previously%20hush-hush%20beef%20between%20Millstein%20and%20Goldfarb%2C%20who%20also%20works%20as%20a%20TV%20writer%20and%20social%20media%20personality.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20July%2C%20Fishwife%20sued%20Goldfarb%2C%20claiming%20that%20she%20and%20her%20father%20were%20refusing%20to%20turn%20over%20access%20to%20the%20company's%20website%2C%20email%2C%20and%20cloud-storage%20accounts%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20get%20a%20bigger%20stake%20in%20the%20company.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMillstein%20%26quot%3Bhas%20devoted%20an%20average%20of%20more%20than%2090%20hours%20per%20week%20to%20growing%20the%20company%2C%20overseeing%20operations%2C%20hiring%20additional%20personnel%2C%20and%20building%20a%20respected%20brand%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20lawsuit%20said.%20%26quot%3BIn%20contrast%2C%20Caroline%20Goldfarb%20worked%20for%20Fishwife%20for%20less%20than%20a%20year%2C%20and%20for%20no%20more%20than%20a%20few%20hours%20per%20week.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20lawsuit%2C%20which%20was%20apparently%20settled%20less%20than%20a%20month%20after%20it%20was%20filed%2C%20made%20no%20waves%20when%20it%20hit%20last%20summer%2C%20perhaps%20because%20it%20was%20filed%20in%20Fishwife's%20lesser-known%20legal%20name%2C%20Shrimp%20Girls%20Inc.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20upsetting%20to%20see%20the%20animosity%20when%20I%20saw%20the%20lawsuit%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20investor%20in%20the%20company%20who%20requested%20anonymity%20due%20to%20potential%20legal%20issues%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan