80%9D%20has%20been%20reached%2C%20whose%20%E2%80%9Ccost%20to%20our%20economic%2C%20societal%2C%20and%20ecological%20stability%20risk%20is%20severe%20%E2%80%94%20and%20growing%20every%20day.%20In%20short%2C%20we%20need%20action%20now.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20say%20their%20drive%20for%20fairer%20taxes%20represents%C2%A0%E2%80%9Ca%20return%20to%20normality%2C%20%E2%80%9D%20arguing%20that%20taxing%20the%20rich%20will%20%E2%80%9Cturn%20extreme%20and%20unproductive%20private%20wealth%20into%20an%20investment%20for%20our%20common%20democratic%20future.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98We%20believe%20we%20must%20be%20taxed%20more%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEvery%20moment%20of%20delay%20entrenches%20the%20dangerous%20economic%20status%20quo%2C%20threatens%20our%20democratic%20norms%2C%20and%20passes%20the%20buck%20to%20our%20children%20and%20grandchildren%2C%E2%80%9D%20write%20the%20signatories%2C%20who%20include%20heiresses%20Valerie%20Rockefeller%2C%20Abigail%20Disney%20and%20Marlene%20Engelhorn%2C%20an%20Austrian%20national%20whose%20forefather%20Friedrich%20Engelhorn%20founded%20German%20chemicals%20company%20BASF.%C2%A0%E2%80%9CNot%20only%20do%20we%20want%20to%20be%20taxed%20more%20but%20we%20believe%20we%20must%20be%20taxed%20more.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEngelhorn%2C%20who%20has%20criticized%20the%20fact%20that%20Austria%20does%20not%20have%20an%20inheritance%20tax%2C%20recently%20made%20the%20headlines%20when%20she%20said%20she%20wanted%20to%20redistribute%20%E2%82%AC25%20million%20(%2427%20million)%20of%20her%20inherited%20wealth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20have%20inherited%20a%20fortune%2C%20and%20therefore%20power%2C%20without%20having%20done%20anything%20for%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20told%20reporters.%20She%20has%20set%20up%20a%20Good%20Council%20for%20Redistribution%20to%20develop%20solutions%20in%20the%20%E2%80%9Cinterest%20of%20society%20as%20a%20whole.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20rich%20get%20richer%20%E2%80%94%20and%20richer%20and%20richer%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fcan-a-wealth-tax-bridge-germanys-divide-between-rich-and-poor%2Fa-50185609%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3Egap%20between%20the%20rich%20and%20the%20poor%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0continues%20to%20widen%20worldwide.%20According%20to%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwir2022.wid.world%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWorld%20Inequality%20Report%202022%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20some%2038%25%20of%20the%20global%20increment%20in%20wealth%20between%201995%20and%202021%20went%20to%20the%20top%201%25.%20Only%202%25%20went%20to%20the%20bottom%20half%2C%20namely%20the%204%20billion%20poorest%20people%20in%20the%20world.%20And%20after%20the%20outbreak%20of%20the%20COVID%20pandemic%20in%202020%2C%20global%20billionaire%20wealth%20rose%20more%20than%20ever.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAround%20the%20world%2C%20there%20have%20already%20been%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fbiden-budget-plan-proposes-higher-taxes-on-the-rich%2Fa-61270998%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3Eseveral%20attempts%20to%20tax%20large%20fortunes%20more.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0For%20example%2C%20in%20the%202019%20presidential%20campaign%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20Senator%20Elizabeth%20Warren%20proposed%20an%20%E2%80%9Cultra-millionaire%20tax%E2%80%9D%20on%20every%20dollar%20of%20net%20worth%20above%20%2450%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20isn%E2%80%99t%20easy%20to%20implement%20such%20measures.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20signatories%20of%20the%20petition%20in%20Davos%20are%20mainly%20heirs%20who%20do%20not%20actively%20run%20a%20company%2C%20and%20therefore%20feel%20uncomfortable%20with%20great%20wealth%20that%20they%20have%20not%20generated%20themselves%2C%E2%80%9D%20explained%20Stefan%20Bach%20from%20the%20German%20Institute%20for%20Economic%20Research%20(DIW)%20in%20Berlin.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20they%20tend%20to%20be%20isolated%20voices.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fworlds-richest-five-men-double-wealth-oxfam%2Fa-67979934%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3Evast%20majority%20of%20the%20super-rich%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0were%20more%20reserved%20in%20this%20regard.%20Indeed%2C%20there%20was%20strong%20political%20resistance%20from%20business%20associations%2C%20which%2C%20thanks%20to%20their%20work%20with%20lobby%20groups%2C%20were%20generally%20well-connected%20to%20high-ranking%20politicians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMany%20large%20fortunes%20are%20also%20tied%20up%20in%20business%2C%E2%80%9D%20Bach%20said.%20The%20idea%2C%20business%20associations%20argue%2C%20is%20that%20low%20taxes%20for%20entrepreneurs%20provide%20incentives%20to%20invest%20and%20create%20jobs%2C%20meaning%20higher%20taxes%20could%20jeopardize%20jobs%20and%20investment%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20potentially%20even%20lead%20to%20company%20heirs%20choosing%20not%20to%20run%20the%20company%20they%20could%20inherit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20argument%20essentially%20stifles%20all%20possible%20political%20debates%20on%20wealth%20or%20inheritance%20taxes%2C%E2%80%9D%20Bach%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEurope%E2%80%99s%20shift%20to%20the%20right%20makes%20change%20unlikely%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGenerally%2C%20it%20does%20not%20make%20sense%20for%20a%20country%20to%20act%20alone%20when%20imposing%20taxes%20on%20large%20fortunes.%20%E2%80%9CBigger%2C%20international%20companies%20and%2C%20of%20course%2C%20the%20super-rich%20all%20play%20to%20the%20tune%20of%20international%20law%2C%E2%80%9D%20continued%20Bach%2C%20explaining%20that%20billionaires%20could%20easily%20relocate%20to%20other%20countries%20with%20more%20favourable%20tax%20legislation.%20%E2%80%9CNothing%20is%20gained%20if%2C%20in%20the%20end%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20only%20the%20well-behaved%20German%20small%20and%20medium-sized%20companies%20that%20get%20fleeced%20because%20they%20remain%20loyal%20to%20their%20country.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20he%20pointed%20out%20that%20generating%20more%20income%20for%20state%20coffers%20through%20a%20balanced%20combination%20of%20tax%20increases%C2%A0on%20the%20top%20income%20bracket%20or%20with%20a%20wealth%20tax%20was%20possible.%20%E2%80%9CBut%2C%20of%20course%2C%20this%20can%20only%20be%20done%20in%20a%20way%20that%20is%20coordinated%20internationally%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20there%20had%20been%20some%20successful%20attempts%20to%20curb%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Ftaxes%2Ft-19021286%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3Etax%20evasion%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0by%20large%20corporations%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20130%20countries%2C%20which%20together%20account%20for%2090%25%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20economic%20output%2C%20had%20also%20agreed%20on%20a%20max%2C%20and%20in%20so%20doing%20were%20trying%20to%20prevent%20companies%20from%20just%20moving%20onto%20other%20countries%20with%20better%20tax%20rates.%20Last%20year%2C%20several%20EU%20lawmakers%20proposed%20a%20similar%20global%20minimum%20tax%20on%20extremely%20high%20private%20wealth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Bach%20doubted%20that%20there%20would%20be%20any%20developments%20on%20this%20front%20in%20the%20near%20future%2C%20and%20this%20was%20partly%20to%20do%20with%20the%20general%20shift%20to%20the%20right%20across%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20are%20hardly%20any%20left-wing%20majorities%20left%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%2C%20explaining%20that%20when%20it%20came%20to%20tax%20measures%2C%20it%20was%20important%20to%20have%20conservative%20and%20liberal%20parties%20on%20board%2C%20but%20these%20were%20inherently%20more%20business-friendly.%20He%20said%20that%20in%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fgermany%2Ft-17871182%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EGermany%2C%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0nothing%20would%20happen%20%E2%80%9Cin%20the%20foreseeable%20future%2C%E