Celsius%20(2.12%20degrees%20Fahrenheit)%20above%20the%2020th-century%20average%20of%2013.9%20degrees%20Celsius%20(57.0%20degrees%20Fahrenheit)%2C%20according%20to%20research%20conducted%20by%20NOAA%E2%80%99s%20National%20Centers%20for%20Environmental%20Information.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2010%20warmest%20years%20since%201850%20have%20now%20all%20occurred%20in%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20as%20global%20mean%20surface%20temperatures%20(land%20and%20sea)%20diverged%200.77%20to%201.18%20degrees%20Celsius%20from%20the%2020th%20century%20average%20between%202014%20and%202023.%20And%20it%E2%80%99s%20unlikely%20that%20the%20planet%E2%80%99s%20hot%20streak%20will%20come%20to%20an%20end%20this%20year.%20According%20to%20NOAA%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20one-in-three%20chance%20that%202024%20will%20be%20warmer%20than%202023%20and%20a%2099%25%20chance%20that%202024%20will%20be%20among%20the%20five%20warmest%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20now%20been%2047%20years%20since%20Earth%20had%20a%20cooler-than-average%20year%20in%201976%2C%20as%20temperatures%20have%20diverged%20upward%20from%20the%2020th%20century%20average%20in%2048%20of%20the%20past%2050%20years.%20Conversely%2C%20just%205%20of%20the%20the%20first%2090%20years%20of%20the%20observance%20period%20(i.e.%201850-1939)%20saw%20global%20surface%20temperatures%20above%20the%2020th%20century%20average%20of%2013.9%20degrees%20Celsius.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAfter%20seeing%20the%202023%20climate%20analysis%2C%20I%20have%20to%20pause%20and%20say%20that%20the%20findings%20are%20astounding%2C%E2%80%9D%20NOAA%20Chief%20Scientist%20Dr.%20Sarah%20Kapnick%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%20%E2%80%9CNot%20only%20was%202023%20the%20warmest%20year%20in%20NOAA%E2%80%99s%20174-year%20climate%20record%20%E2%80%93%20it%20was%20the%20warmest%20by%20far.%20A%20warming%20planet%20means%20we%20need%20to%20be%20prepared%20for%20the%20impacts%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statista.com%2Ftopics%2F1148%2Fglobal-climate-change%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclimate%20change%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20are%20happening%20here%20and%20now%2C%20like%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statista.com%2Fstatistics%2F1101796%2Fnumber-billion-dollar-climate-disasters-events-decade%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eextreme%20weather%20events%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20become%20both%20more%20frequent%20and%20severe.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Infographic%3A%202023%20Was%20the%20Warmest%20Year%20on%20Record%20-%20by%20a%20Record%20Margin%20%7C%20Statista%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statista.com%2Fchart%2F28722%2Fglobal-surface-temperature-anomalies%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Infographic%3A%202023%20Was%20the%20Warmest%20Year%20on%20Record%20-%20by%20a%20Record%20Margin%20%7C%20Statista%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.statcdn.com%2FInfographic%2Fimages%2Fnormal%2F28722.jpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cem%3EYou%20will%20find%20more%20infographics%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statista.com%2Fchartoftheday%2F%5C%22%3EStatista%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20this%20article%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statista.com%2Fchart%2F28722%2Fglobal-surface-temperature-anomalies%2F%3Futm_source%3DStatista%2BNewsletters%26utm_campaign%3D8caa187f2b-COM_DailyData_Thu_KW03_2024_FRi%26utm_medium%3Demail%26utm_term%3D0_-53a33ddf1e-%255BLIST_EMAIL_ID%255D%5C%22%3Eoriginally%20published%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705634707000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F19084906%2Fmarkus-spiske-iZYJzBWXfYA-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fchart-2023-was-the-warmest-year-on-record-by-a-record-margin%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22There's%20a%20one-in-three%20chance%20that%202024%20will%20be%20warmer%20than