further.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FMoosaZameer%2Fstatus%2F1747999315363324411%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3EThe%20Maldivian%20minister%20noted%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20that%20they%20%E2%80%9Cexchanged%20views%20on%20the%20ongoing%20high-level%20discussions%20on%20the%20withdrawal%20of%20Indian%20military%20personnel%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWriting%20that%20it%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9Cpleasure%E2%80%9D%20to%20meet%20with%20Jaishankar%2C%20Zameer%20wrote%20that%20they%20also%20discussed%20completion%20of%20ongoing%20development%20projects%20in%20Maldives%20and%20cooperation%20within%20SAARC%20and%20NAM.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20committed%20to%20further%20strengthening%20and%20expanding%20our%20cooperation%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20posted%20on%20his%20official%20X%20account.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20their%20first%20meeting%20since%20a%20new%20government%20under%20President%20Mohamed%20Muizzu%20took%20over%20in%20November%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20being%20sworn%20in%2C%20Muizzu%2C%20who%20had%20campaigned%20for%20the%20removal%20of%20the%20Indian%20military%20during%20the%20presidential%20election%2C%20made%20a%20formal%20request%20for%20their%20withdrawal%20to%20New%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20Muizzu%E2%80%99s%20meeting%20with%20the%20Indian%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20at%20Dubai%2C%20both%20sides%20announced%20that%20a%20group%20of%20senior%20officials%20will%20discuss%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20meeting%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98core%20group%E2%80%99%20was%20held%20in%20Mal%C3%A9%20on%20January%2014%2C%20where%20Maldives%20laid%20down%20the%20deadline%20of%20March%2015%20for%20withdrawal%20of%20Indian%20security%20personnel.%20While%20Maldives%20talked%20about%20withdrawal%2C%20the%20Indian%20press%20note%20only%20referred%20to%20%E2%80%9Cmutually%20workable%20solution%20to%20enable%20continued%20operation%20of%20Indian%20aviation%20platforms%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20week%2C%20India%2